.TH "hid_modify_dquirk" 9 "hid_modify_dquirk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hid_modify_dquirk \- add/replace a HID quirk
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hid_modify_dquirk
.BI "(const struct hid_device_id *id "  ","
.BI "const unsigned long quirks "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "id" 12
the HID device to match
.IP "quirks" 12
the unsigned long quirks value to add/replace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If an dynamic quirk exists in memory for this device, replace its
quirks value with what was provided.  Otherwise, add the quirk
to the dynamic quirks list.
.SH "RETURN"
0 OK, -error on failure.
